main event: Two or three bright, large lights were seen moving in a peculiar manner by a military observer in the Far East on April 14, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were described as having measured or described speed, movement, or course, but other data was insufficient to classify them as astronomical, missile, or aircraft phenomena.
The report was deemed to have insufficient information to evaluate the sighting for possible action.
Another report from February 17, 1961 mentioned the possibility of the object being a sentry body (or Canopus), anomalous propagation, or equipment malfunction.
A report from February 28, 1961 indicated the possibility of the objects being related to some USAF activities, such as a chuff exercise.
The sighting was labeled as an observation of an unidentified flying object.
sighted object: two or three bright, large lights
